solution: ```class Solution {
    public int minimizedStringLength(String s) {
        boolean[] seen = new boolean[26];
        int unique = 0;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) {
            int idx = c - 'a';
            if (!seen[idx]) {
                seen[idx] = true;
                unique++;
            }
        }
        return unique;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Any character can be removed except one occurrence of each distinct character, so the minimal length equals the number of distinct characters.

